# Architecture Guardrails

- Hot-path implementation is Rust + Tokio.
- Prefer one Rust binary with explicit internal modules until complexity justifies splitting.
- Use WebSockets for live market data; use REST for startup, recovery, and metadata.
- Persist raw feed messages and normalized events so every decision can be replayed and audited.
- Live paper mode and replay mode must share the same normalized event model.
- Optimize for correctness, auditability, deterministic replay, and risk control before live speed.
- Keep implementation choices tied to `PRD.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, and `IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`.
